│ check if `RetVal` is actually an `Instruction` before attempting to cast it and set overflow flags. If it's a    │
│ `ConstantExpr`, we cannot set overflow flags on it, so we should skip this step.\n\n5. Conclusion: By adding a   │
│ check for `isa<Instruction>(RetVal)` before casting, we prevent the assertion failure while still allowing the   │
│ optimization to proceed correctly. The overflow flag propagation is only relevant for actual instructions        │
│ anyway, so skipping it for constant expressions is the correct behavior."})                                      │
